arded%20when%20a%20country%20can%20prove%20it%20has%20interrupted%20the%20transmission%20of%20malaria%20for%20at%20least%20three%20consecutive%20years.%20Malaria%20still%20claims%20the%20lives%20of%20at%20least%20600%2C000%20people%20annually%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20whom%20are%20in%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20statement%2C%20the%20WHO%20commended%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Egyptian%20government%20and%20people%26quot%3B%20for%20their%20successful%20efforts%20to%20%26quot%3Bend%20a%20disease%20that%20has%20been%20present%20in%20the%20country%20since%20ancient%20times.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgypt%20is%20now%20the%20third%20country%20in%20the%20WHO's%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%20Region%20to%20receive%20this%20certification%2C%20following%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20and%20Morocco.%20Globally%2C%20a%20total%20of%2044%20countries%20and%20one%20territory%20have%20reached%20this%20milestone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20emphasized%20that%20this%20certification%20marks%20%26quot%3Bthe%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20phase%2C%26quot%3B%20urging%20Egypt%20to%20remain%20vigilant%20in%20order%20to%20maintain%20its%20malaria-free%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20certification%2C%20a%20country%20must%20demonstrate%20its%20ability%20to%20prevent%20the%20re-establishment%20of%20malaria%20transmission.%20The%20WHO%20highlighted%20that%20Egypt's%20initial%20attempts%20to%20reduce%20human-mosquito%20contact%20began%20in%20the%201920s%20by%20restricting%20rice%20cultivation%20and%20other%20agricultural%20crops%20near%20residential%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMalaria%2C%20caused%20by%20a%20parasite%20transmitted%20through%20mosquito%20bites%2C%20has%20seen%20progress%20in%20control%20efforts%2C%20with%20vaccines%20now%20being%20deployed%20in%20some%20regions.%20However%2C%20monitoring%20the%20disease%20and%20preventing%20mosquito%20bites%20remain%20the%20most%20effective%20preventive%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReceiving%20the%20malaria%20elimination%20certificate%20today%20is%20not%20the%20end%20of%20the%20journey%20but%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20phase%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Egypt's%20Health%20Minister%2C%20Khaled%20Abdel%20Ghaffar.%20%26quot%3BWe%20must%20now%20work%20tirelessly%20and%20vigilantly%20to%20sustain%20our%20achievement%20through%20maintaining%20the%20highest%20standards%20for%20surveillance%2C%20diagnosis%2C%20and%20treatment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201940s%2C%20malaria%20cases%20in%20Egypt%20surged%20to%20over%20three%20million%20due%20to%20population%20displacement%20during%20World%20War%20II.%20The%20construction%20of%20the%20Aswan%20Dam%20in%20the%201960s%20also%20increased%20malaria%20risks%20by%20creating%20mosquito%20breeding%20grounds%20through%20standing%20water.%20However%2C%20by%202001%2C%20Egypt%20had%20brought%20malaria%20%26quot%3Bfirmly%20under%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Nigeria%20continues%20to%20bear%20the%20highest%20malaria%20burden%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20all%20malaria%20deaths%20globally%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%2C%20Uganda%2C%20and%20Mozambique.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729521720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fk7qbgqbg_mosquito-_625x300_21_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftruly-historic-egypt-certified-malaria-free-by-who-after-100-year-effort-6840771%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%201940s%2C%20malaria%20cases%20in%20Egypt%20surged%20to%20over%20three%20million%20due%20to%20population%20displacement%20during%20World%20War%20II.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftruly-historic-egypt-certified-malaria-free-by-who-after-100-year-effort-6840771%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%